  "lock_statement": "Recoverability is measured by how much recoverable organizational structure survives passage through a phase corridor. Recoverability is transported through corridors: the corridor acts as a medium, recoverability acts as the transported quantity, burden acts as attenuation, fragility measures decay rate, and retention measures transmission efficiency. Phase corridors therefore possess not only width, intensity, and accumulated burden, but also recoverability retention. Multi-seed toy-model results support the principle that recoverability retention decreases as accumulated corridor burden increases. A corridor is navigable only if recoverability survives traversal."
